{
  "$version": 1,
  "name": "membership",
  "alias": "membership",
  "namespace": "Stackra\\Finance\\Membership",
  "description": "The customer's paid subscription contract with the academy. Answers 'is this athlete paying to attend this academy this month?'. FUNDAMENTALLY DISTINCT from TenantSubscription — TenantSubscription is the academy paying Stackra for SaaS; Membership is the parent paying the academy for their athlete. Owns FOUR aggregates: Membership (the contract — belongs to Tenant + Region + Branch + Athlete; references MembershipPlan; has lifecycle pending/active/paused/cancelled/lapsed/refunded/expired), MembershipPlan (the SKU catalog per branch — name / price_cents / currency / billing_interval / pass_grant_config), MembershipRenewal (per-period auto-renewal record — one row per billing cycle with attempt count + payment_intent_id + terminal status), Pass (per-session admission credit — a monthly plan grants N passes each period; each session check-in consumes one). Money flow: Membership.creating triggers Invoice.create in the same transaction; Invoice.paid triggers Membership.status=active + Pass generation for the period. Membership renewal is atomic: MembershipRenewal.create → PaymentIntent.confirm → on success: extend Membership.expires_at + generate next-period Passes; on failure: retry ladder (day+3, day+7, day+14) with dunning notifications, then Membership.status=lapsed after 3 failed renewals. Cancellation flow: soft-cancel by-period-end (default) vs hard-cancel + prorated refund (Enterprise entitlement). Membership carries frozen tax_calculation_snapshot at contract signing (immutable — mid-contract VAT changes never retroactively re-tax). All money flows PCI-DSS compliant — payment tokens live in the payment module, never in memberships. Never conflate with TenantSubscription: memberships.tenant_id is the ACADEMY (recipient of the money); tenant_subscriptions.tenant_id is the ACADEMY (payer of the money to Stackra).",
